Prepare pie crust as directed on package for a baked ready-to-fill crust; cool. Microwave chocolate in medium microwaveable bowl on HIGH 1 min.; stir until chocolate is completely melted. Stir in 1 cup of the whipped topping. Spread evenly onto bottom of crust; set aside. Add milk to dry pudding mixes. Beat with wire whisk 2 min. or until well blended. Pour over chocolate layer in crust. Refrigerate at least 4 hours. Top with the remaining 1 cup whipped topping and the strawberries just before serving. Store leftovers in refrigerator.